none: Scholar and politician Yi Hyo-sang (1906-1986) published poems he wrote while he was a teacher around the time of liberation. Yi had studied in Tokyo University in Japan and served as the chairman of the National Assembly in South Korea. He was also a professor at Kyŏngbuk National University.
